#MOBILE
Vnum       1000
Keywords   spirit male human greet~
Short      &Wa spirit&w~
Long       &WA spirit of a male human is here greeting newcomers.&w
~
Desc       &WThe spirit here is a glowing form a male human whose features
are not very distinguishable to the eye. He is here greeting
those that are new to the village.
~
Race       magical~
Class      fighter~
Position   mounted~
DefPos     mounted~
Gender     male~
Actflags   npc sentinel pacifist~
Affected   truesight~
Stats1     0 1 0 0 10 0 0 0 0 0
Stats2     1 10 5
Stats3     1 4 0
Stats4     2 13 1 0 0 0 15
Attribs    10 10 10 10 10 10 10
Saves      0 0 0 0 0 0
#MUDPROG
Progtype  greet_prog~
Arglist   100~
Comlist   if isaffected($n) == spirit
sayto $n Greetings. I heard that you were coming and I am here to
sayto $n help you understand what comes next. You have many options
sayto $n available to you.
mpsleep 2
sayto $n You can return back to the material or mortal plane via the
sayto $n following methods...
mpsleep 2
mea $n &YSupplication&w
mea $n &YReincarnation&w
mea $n &YPacts&w
mea $n &YSpells&w
mea $n &YOrb Hunting&w
mea $n &YCorpse Hunting&w
mer $n &WThe spirit shows &W$n&W some options.
mpsleep 2
sayto $n Let me know which option you would like to hear about first.
mpsleep 2
sayto $n Once you hear all the options let me know if you
sayto $n would like to also hear about your new &YSpirit Life&W.
else
chuckle
sayto $n Welcome to Frostmeet, warmblood.
endif
~
#ENDPROG

#MUDPROG
Progtype  speech_prog~
Arglist   p supplication~
Comlist   If isaffected($n) == spirit
Sayto $n If you are following a deity and are in good favor
Sayto $n with them there is a chance you can use the 
Sayto $n supplicate command to bring yourself back to the
Sayto $n living. 
Mpsleep 2
Sayto $n Deity supplication uses FAVOR and you will need to
Sayto $n have enough before you can use supplication.
Mpsleep 2
Sayto $n If you lack the favor required you may try praying at
Sayto $n the temple nearby to see if your deity is listening.
Mpsleep 2
Sayto $n For more information check out HELP SUPPLICATE
Sayto $n and HELP PRAY.
Else
Chuckle
Sayto $n You do not need that information, warmblood.
Endif
~
#ENDPROG

#MUDPROG
Progtype  speech_prog~
Arglist   p reincarnation~
Comlist   If isaffected($n) == spirit
Sayto $n Reincarnation should be considered a last resort
Sayto $n for those trying to return to the living. When one
sayto $n chooses to reincarnate they give up one stat point
Sayto $n that is randomly chosen by fate.
Mpsleep 2
sayto $n You return to the living, but you could be weaker,
Sayto $n less attractive, or less intelligent.
Mpsleep 2
Sayto $n You are advised to use this when all of the other
Sayto $n options are unavailable.
Else
Chuckle
Sayto $n You do not need that information, warmblood.
Endif
~
#ENDPROG

#MUDPROG
Progtype  speech_prog~
Arglist   p pacts~
Comlist   If isaffected($n) == spirit
Sayto $n Often a mortal will make a pact with some sort of
Sayto $n patron, which can help that mortal return to the
Sayto $n living. Often these patrons will require you to do
Sayto $n something in the mortal realm that will complete
Sayto $n the pact.
Mpsleep 2
Sayto $n Patrons can be found hiding in this village despite
Sayto $n our efforts to drive them out. Their offers can be
Sayto $n dangerous or even go against your moral code so
Sayto $n if you choose this route you are warned.
Mpsleep 2
Sayto $n If you did not complete the pact and return here again
Sayto $n you will find that patron to be very upset with you. It
Sayto $n is possible that they will refuse to help you until the
Sayto $n original pact is complete. This often results in a few
Sayto $n unprepared souls becoming permanent residents here.
mpsleep 2
sayto $n Only agree to a pact if you will complete it right
sayto $n away upon being returned to the material plane.
Mpsleep 2
Sayto $n For more information you check out HELP DEATHPACTS.
Else
Chuckle
Sayto $n You do not need that information, warmblood.
Endif
~
#ENDPROG

#MUDPROG
Progtype  speech_prog~
Arglist   p spells~
Comlist   If isaffected($n) == spirit
Sayto $n If you were traveling with a skilled healer then perhaps
Sayto $n they are currently working to use a spell such as RAISE
Sayto $n DEAD or RESURRECTION to bring you back to life. They
Sayto $n could also take you to a temple and have the Cleric there
Sayto $n bring you back. These are the more Qylain accepted
Sayto $n methods of being brought back to life
Mpsleep 2
Sayto $n The other more.. nefarious way.. Is to use a spell like
Sayto $n CLONE, which allows a magic user to awaken in a new
Sayto $n body somewhere else upon death. There are a few others
Sayto $n that ward off death or conditions that stop it from happening.
Sayto $n Many of the Qylain faith seek to stop such practices as it
Sayto $n interferes with the natural order of things.
Mpsleep 2
Sayto $n If you know someone is going to bring you back you are
Sayto $n welcome to visit around the village until then. You need to
Sayto $n stay out of the &ROOC&W tavern if you are waiting or else
Sayto $n their spell will fail upon casting.
Else
Sayto $n For more information you can seek out the help files on
Sayto $n the spells discussed such as RAISE DEAD.
Chuckle
Sayto $n You do not need that information, warmblood.
Endif
~
#ENDPROG

#MUDPROG
Progtype  speech_prog~
Arglist   p orb hunting~
Comlist   If isaffected($n) == spirit
Sayto $n Those that seek a way back to the living can be
sayto $n employed by our local ranger. Soul orbs are residual
Sayto $n necrotic energy that comes from the act of dying on the
Sayto $n material plane. If left where it is it can infect the area 
Sayto $n surrounding it causing decay. We recycle this energy to 
Sayto $n maintain this plane.
Mpsleep 2
Sayto $n The amount of orbs needed to be collected by someone
Sayto $n is dependent on how advanced of an adventurer they are.
Mpsleep 2
Sayto $n You will find that the more advanced the longer this hunting
Sayto $n can take while young adventurers just starting out can be
Sayto $n done much quicker.
Mpsleep 2
Sayto $n Seek out Martivus at his home here in the village if you
Sayto $n wish to hunt orbs for the village. He is our hunter and will
Sayto $n have much more to say on this task.
Else
Sayto $n For more information check out HELP ORBHUNTING.
Chuckle
Sayto $n You do not need that information, warmblood.
Endif
~
#ENDPROG

#MUDPROG
Progtype  speech_prog~
Arglist   p Corpse Hunting~
Comlist   If isaffected($n) == spirit
Whistle
Sayto $n Now that is an advanced method and requires a skilled
Sayto $n adventurer. This method requires a spirit such as yourself
Sayto $n to find a way off of Icynth and back to the material plane.
Mpsleep 2
Sayto $n Once there you would need to navigate the realms until
Sayto $n you find your body where you would re-enter it.
Mpsleep 2
Sayto $n However, you do not have a large window of opportunity
Sayto $n here. Upon death the spiritual cord between you and your
Sayto $n corpse begins to diminish until it fades away permanently. 
Sayto $n If you do not make it to your body in time you will become 
Sayto $n stuck on that plane as what the warmbloods call a ghost.
Mpsleep 2
Sayto $n You can still be brought back by warmblood spells while
Sayto $n stuck on the material plane, but you must be in the same
Sayto $n area in order for it to work. While in Icynth you can be
Sayto $n anywhere and their spells will bring you to them, which is
Sayto $n the benefit of being here versus the material plane as a
Sayto $n ghost.
Mpsleep 2
Sayto $n Also while you are on the material plane as a ghost, you
Sayto $n will need to avoid soul hunters. These trained spirits are on
Sayto $n the material plane with the task of returning wayward souls
Sayto $n back here to Icynth. If you are caught you will be sent back
Sayto $n and imprisoned for some time. While imprisoned you cannot
Sayto $n return to the living until the sentence is finished. Being a 
Sayto $n ghost is frowned upon by Qylaith and those that worship her.
Else
Sayto $n For more information check out HELP DEATH.
Chuckle
Sayto $n You do not need that information, warmblood.
Endif
~
#ENDPROG

#MUDPROG
Progtype  speech_prog~
Arglist   p spirit life~
Comlist   if isaffected($n) == spirit
nod $n
sayto $n Until you are returned to life you will roam the planes as
sayto $n a spirit. Some choose after some time to stay here and live in
sayto $n peace while others like to return to the material plane of
sayto $n of the "Warmbloods."
mpsleep 2
sayto $n As a spirit you can fly, walk through doors that are
sayto $n not enchanted to block such, and travel great distances.
sayto $n Mortals will need to cast the spell SPEAK WITH DEAD in
sayto $n order to see you if you go to the mortal plane. They will
sayto $n see you just fine if they visit here.
mpsleep 2
sayto $n That spell also allows them to talk to you and also hear what
sayto $n you say back. Some spirits have been known to possess
sayto $n warmbloods or create hauntings.
mpsleep 2
sayto $n As a spirit you will not have hunger or require something
sayto $n to drink... although we have some great taverns here in the
sayto $n village. You will also have no need to sleep as well.
mpsleep 2
sayto $n I hope you enjoy your stay here whether it is short or forever.
else
sayto $n I have nothing to offer you, warmblood.
endif
~
#ENDPROG

#ENDMOBILE

