#EXDESC
ExDescKey    zhyran~
ExDesc       &CYou see a large model of a city that had curved styling in terms
of walls, buildings, and even the castle. All of the architecture
was known for its rhythm and wild looking shapes. Zhyran was known
as the "City of Sound," which is attributed to its love of bards
and the arts - especially music. The city was once in the Crystal
Mountains until during the Great Rift it was destroyed when the
elder bards there tried to use song to protect the city. The magics
backfired and drove the city deep into the mountains where it was
never seen or heard from again...
~
#ENDEXDESC

#EXDESC
ExDescKey    Kaltas~
ExDesc       &YYou see a large kingdom set upon the sands of a desert. The buildings
in the city portion are trimmed with gold and the city seems to
shine. The ancient kingdom of Kaltas was known for its vast riches
and being a mecca of trade. It amassed a great fortune until the day
it was destroyed. The ruling family of Kaltas had waged war upon the
city of Parinath. In a vain attempt to harness magic from an unknown
source the city was obliterated by this experimentation. Some say that
they were punished by Crisma for tainting a source of ancient
magic. The city was swallowed by the desert over time and forgotten...
~
#ENDEXDESC

#EXDESC
ExDescKey    zyndale~
ExDesc       &GThe lost village of Zyndale was once part of the network of human
villages referred to as "The Dales." This particular village was
home to the gnome Archmage Rhemig Helvel. Helvel was a well established
illusionist and was experimenting with an ancient source of travel
magic when it destroyed the village. Some say that at night the village
restores itself and the villagers walk till dawn comes...
~
#ENDEXDESC

#EXDESC
ExDescKey    llekwyn~
ExDesc       &PYou see a large stone model of a library that also served as a
temple for the goddess Omunae. The exterior was painted a deep
shade of purple and was trimmed in gold. As you walk around the model
you see the interior view, which shows it had many floors and each
floor was dedicated to a various study. At the top of the library
was the temple space and home of the clergy. When the great city of
Kaltas was destroyed this library was moved by Omunae to somewhere
in the desert to avoid its knowledge from being used again to wage
war. Omunae buried the library and also entrusted a servant to
watch over the library from intruders...
~
#ENDEXDESC

#EXDESC
ExDescKey    models~
ExDesc       &wYou see various models and each has a plaque with information
attached. Perhaps you can investigate the models to learn more...
~
#ENDEXDESC

#MUDPROG
Progtype  cmd_prog~
Arglist   p investigate models~
Comlist   if investigation($n) >= 12
mea $n You examine the models and discover the following...
mpsleep 2
mea $n You see that each model has a plaque with info. You can learn
mea $n more about the following places:
mpsleep 2
mea $n &CZhyran: The City of Sound&w
mea $n &YThe Kingdom of Kaltas
mea $n &wThe Village of Zyndale
mea $n &pThe Great Library of Llekwyn&w
mpsleep 2
mea $n To learn more simply LOOK <NAME> such as LOOK ZHYRAN.
mer $n $n examines a plaque near the models.
else
mea $n You fail to find anything.
endif
~
#ENDPROG

