#EXDESC
ExDescKey    Thudrin~
ExDesc       &YThe dwarven god Thudrin was the patron of dwarves and smithing. He
was a stern god who did not enjoy failure. He was known for his white hair
and beard as well as an eye patch to hide the missing eye he lost during
a battle with the orcish god Urkmash. His wife Genda was known for
soothing his ego and anger by merely touching him.
 
Thudrin sacrificed himself during the Great Rift to help stabilize
the realm and save his dwarven children from annihilation. He gave
part of his essence to the dwarven engineer, Dhordolim, whom he charged
with watching over his children.
~
#ENDEXDESC

#EXDESC
ExDescKey    genda~
ExDesc       &YThe dwarven goddess Genda was the matron of the dwarves and 
was the goddess of dwarven love, aesthetics, and the family. She
was a calm, nuturing goddess with a very powerful temper that
she rarely showed. She was a beautiful goddess who was known
for her fiery red mane that touched the floor lightly.
 
&YGenda sacrificed herself during the Great Rift to help stabilize
the realm and save her dwarven children from annihilation. She
gave part of her essence to the new god Dhordolim, whom she charged
with watching over her children.
~
#ENDEXDESC

#EXDESC
ExDescKey    raarg~
ExDesc       &YThe dwarven god Raarg was the child of Thudrin and Genda. He was
the dwarven god of war and protection. He was a wild god who
was the epitome of the "dwarven temper." He had his mother's red
hair and his beard was said to be stained with the blood of his
enemies.
 
&YRaarg was forced by his parents to sacrifice himself during the
Great Rift to help stabilize the realm and save the dwarves. He
gave part of his essence to Dhordolim, whom he charged with
watching over the dwarves. It is said this essence is what made
Dhordolim a bit more aggressive in his pursuits.
~
#ENDEXDESC

#EXDESC
ExDescKey    lolth~
ExDesc       &zThe drow spider goddess Lolth was known for driving her followers
to fight amongst themselves and with the surface dwellers of Aerix. She
was a vengeful goddess with a jealous streak and loved to sacrifice
her own followers.
 
&zDuring the Great Rift the goddess watched from her Underdark
prison as the other gods and legendary creatures battled. Using
their weakeness she broke the divine magics that kept her and
her drow from reaching the surface. She led them into battle
against the human kingdoms until she was driven back with the
help of the human patron god, Soarin, and the elven pantheon
of gods. Unknown to Lolth was that the goddess Khaersyx had
snuck into the Underdark and awaited for the weakened Spider
Queen to be sent back. Khaersyx murdered Lolth and took over
her divine portfolios and escaped the Underdark before it
was resealed.
~
#ENDEXDESC

#EXDESC
ExDescKey    urkmash~
ExDesc       &RThe orc god Urkmash was known for his bloodthirst and attempts to
lead his followers against the elven kingdom of Elheleska. Urkmash
would appear to his followers as a red skinned orc with bright
green eyes. He also helped create Half-Orcs by willing his followers
to take capture and take human mates. It is said that these
half-orcs can still hear him or something whispering to them.
 
Urkmash was an ancient deity and was destroyed during the great
100 year war with the elven gods. During these wars Urkmash
was successful in taking out one of Thudrin the dwarven god's eyes
as he tried to protect the elven god Lornas. It is said that
Thudrin never forgave Lornas for this maiming and may be the
root of dislike between elves and dwarves. By their combined
might the elven and dwarven gods destroyed Urkmash. However, he
willed his divine portfolios and essence to Theuros and lives
on in the god of war.
~
#ENDEXDESC

#EXDESC
ExDescKey    rowyrm~
ExDesc       &OThe dragonborn god Rowyrm was once a powerful dragon who rose
to divine levels. His wife Vhirmeath and him gave birth to the
dragonborn and he was their patron god. He was a noble god who
saw the potential of his children to rise up and thwart evil.
 
Rowyrm met his end while his wife and him battled against the
evil gods and creatures who started the Great Rift. Rowyrm used
his divine essence to block his wife from sacrificing herself
as well and to help stabilize the tower of Soronys. He willed
the last of his divine portfolios to his wife as he faded
away.
~
#ENDEXDESC

#EXDESC
ExDescKey    grimvia~
ExDesc       &OThe halfling goddess Grimvia Gladewell was a lighthearted matron of
the halflings. She was known to be very supportive of their efforts to
meet other races and advance their own communities. This goddess
was known for her love of music and laughter.
 
Sadly the goddess perished during the Great Rift - She used her body to
combine with the tower of Soronys in what was once the city called
Darkhaven. This was the final act that helped make the tower become
an anchor for all of the planes. The act also bonded her with the
tower and it was said that those who enter it can sometimes hear her
charmful giggle. Once the Great Rift was over the remaining gods
elected the halfling ranger, Shamis, to godhood and gave him
her divine portfolios to watch over.
~
#ENDEXDESC

#EXDESC
ExDescKey    grimvia gladewell~
ExDesc       &OThe halfling goddess Grimvia Gladewell was a lighthearted matron of
the halflings. She was known to be very supportive of their efforts to
meet other races and advance their own communities. This goddess
was known for her love of music and laughter.
 
Sadly the goddess perished during the Great Rift - She used her body to
combine with the tower of Soronys in what was once the city called
Darkhaven. This was the final act that helped make the tower become
an anchor for all of the planes. The act also bonded her with the
tower and it was said that those who enter it can sometimes hear her
charmful giggle. Once the Great Rift was over the remaining gods
elected the halfling true friend, Shamis, to godhood and gave him
her divine portfolios to watch over.
~
#ENDEXDESC

#EXDESC
ExDescKey    sacuth~
ExDesc       &WThe gnome patron god Sacuth was a jester like god who taught
gnomes how to be mischievous, playful, and curious. He was also
the gnome god of illusions and illusionists. He would play tricks
on his followers to keep their wits sharp.
 
Sacuth and his wife Triasen were the first victims of the dark gods
and creatures that started the Great Rift. Their divine energies
were used to start tearing apart the bonds of the planes by having
their divine blood spilled over those energy connections. Once the
Great Rift was over the remaining gods chose the High Priestess of
the gnome faiths, Phywa Manypurse, to assume the role of gnome
patron along with some other divine portfolios.
~
#ENDEXDESC

#EXDESC
ExDescKey    triasen~
ExDesc       &WTriasen was the gnome goddess of jewels, money, wealth, and fair
deals. She was known to always wear extravagant clothing and jewelry
made from the rarest stones. She was the stern voice in the relationship
with her trickster husband Sacuth.
 
Triasen and Sacuth were the first to be murdered during the Great Rift
and their divine blood was used as a spell component. Triasen tried
to save her husband from death, but was killed first and drained of
all her blood. It is said that some rare jewels of potent divine
magic made from her solidified blood exist and can be found.
~
#ENDEXDESC

#EXDESC
ExDescKey    lornas~
ExDesc       &CLornas was the main elven patron and was known as the "King of the
Fair." He was a stern, stoic deity while his wife, Elenrian, was known
as the softer side. He had a great working relationship with the
dwarven god Thudrin and the two often hunted together. This friendship
lasted until Thudrin was maimed trying to save Lornas from the
orc god Urkmash.
 
&CLornas, like all of the elven gods, sacrificed himself to save
the realms during the Great Rift. He lent his energies to stabilize
the planes and his last act was to select the elven priestess
Aerilaya to take his divine portfolios. Aerilaya was also given
some additional portfolios by the human pantheon as they
welcomed her to their universal pantheon.
~
#ENDEXDESC

#EXDESC
ExDescKey    elenrian~
ExDesc       &CThe elven goddess of love and the arts was known for her soothing
nature, which she used on her stern husband Lornas. She was known
as the most beautiful elf to have ever existed and let that 
charisma to her children. She had long golden tresses that seemed
to have a life of their own. Her name is still honored as part
of the Elheleska name.
 
Elenrian sacrificed herself along with the other elven gods to
help save the realms during the Great Rift. She lent the last of
her divine portfolio to the chosen new goddess Aerilaya before
she disappeared. It is said that all musical instruments and
artistic tools such as paint or brushes failed to work for
almost a year after she died.
~
#ENDEXDESC

#EXDESC
ExDescKey    grimvia gladewell~
#ENDEXDESC

#EXDESC
ExDescKey    fynar~
ExDesc       &CThe elven god of nature, rangers, and the balance was known
for his odd sense of humor. Fynar would often appear to his
followers as a beast with an strange color such as a lilac colored
bear. He was a fair minded deity and charged his followers with
being open minded.
 
Fynar met his end during the Great Rift when he murdered by the
dark gods and creatures that were using divine blood to rip
apart the bonds between the planes. In his dying act he gave
his divine essence and portfolios to the other elven gods in
attempt to strengthen them.
~
#ENDEXDESC

#EXDESC
ExDescKey    rilawen~
ExDesc       The elven goddess of elven magic was known for her eclectic personality.
She charged her followers with researching ancient texts to find long
lost magic. During her life elven magic flourished and was strong.
 
Rilawen was fatally injured during the battle to drive Lolth back
into the Underdark during the Great Rift. Dying of a fast poison
injected into her by the Spider Queen she used her last act to
bolster the goddess Crisma with her divine portfolio. The act was
seen by the elven people as the "True Trust," which ended elven
hostilities towards humans. For many years after her death all
elven magic was unable to work until Crisma was able to master it.
~
#ENDEXDESC

#EXDESC
ExDescKey    Weletar~
ExDesc       &CThe elven god of justice, law, and knights was known for his
judgemental personality. He had a very black and white view of the
realms and did not tolerate vagueness. He was not overly liked by
the other elven gods, but was understood to be very vital none the less.
 
Weletar was defeated as he tried to protect the remaining elven gods
as they lent their energies to stop the Great Rift. His last act was
to give his remaining divine essence to the Lornas and Elenrian before
disappearing. Upon his death the elven "Order of Weletar" were found
dead in their temple as they had sent their life force to Weletar to
help him in his final act.
~
#ENDEXDESC

#EXDESC
ExDescKey    vorpix~
ExDesc       &zThe dark god Vorpix was a demigod revered by evil humans that committed
dark acts to please their lord. Vorpix was a powerful wizard and was
known as the "Laughing Skull," which was attributed to the fact he was
a lich before ascending to demigod status. He did so with the help of his
goddess Khaersyx. The goddess viewed him as a "son" and sought to raise
him to power during the Great Rift. 
 
During the Great Rift Vorpix helped Khaersyx kill the goddess Lloth, which
he siphoned some of her divine essence to rise to godhood. At some point
before the Great Rift was over he was stopped and destroyed by Honeth
before he could take more divine energy. This act branded Honeth the number
one enemy of Khaersyx forever.
 
It is said that a powerful cult has risen to help raise the Laughing Skull
back to life and to godhood again...
~
#ENDEXDESC

